provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1" # Specify your region
}

resource "aws_route53_zone" "reverse_zone" {
  name = "2.1.168.in-addr.arpa" # Example: update based on your network configuration
}

resource "aws_route53_record" "ptr_record" {
  zone_id = aws_route53_zone.reverse_zone.zone_id
  name    = "192.168.1.2" # Reverse IP address needed for PTR record
  type    = "PTR"
  ttl     = "300"
  records = ["host.example53.com."]
}
```

**Note:** Replace the `name` in `aws_route53_zone.reverse_zone` and `name` in `aws_route53_record.ptr_record` with values specific to your network configuration. The `name` in `aws_route53_record.ptr_record` should be the reverse of the IP address for which the PTR record is being created. For example, if the IP address is `192.168.1.2`, the name should be `2.1.168.192.in-addr.arpa`. Adjust the zone name and IP address according to your needs.

