```

This configuration sets up an Amazon Managed Streaming for Kafka (MSK) cluster with three broker instances within a specified AWS managed VPC. and subnets. It also creates AWS security group rules for the MSK nodes. These brokers and the Zookeeper nodes use a `Security Group` to allow all traffic while outside the cluster they are configured to allow only the traffic from your client's subnet. MSK Kafka brokers, in addition to the security group, are configured for encryption in transit using AWS KMS, and for encryption at rest using SSSE-KMS. These settings allow data to be transfer in encrypted form, and stored on disk encrypted as well. 

Note that you should replace paths to specific keys and middleware, such as change `Tagging out to all traffic` and `clients`' traffic. Also adjust the regions and respective IDs. The ami data resources will point to the default Amazon AMI with an Amazon Linux AMI that uses an EBS volume, as the root device.

Please note: You might need additional resources like the KMS key itself and additional roles for MSK access that aren't covered in this basic setup. Adjustments may be necessary depending on your specific environment or requirements.

