  settings {
    disk_size_gb   = 100 # Replicas do not need as much Disk space as an instance, in this case, we allocate 100 GB for provisions per replica.
    disk_type      = "pd-ssd"
  }
}

resource "google_sql_database_instance" "write-replica-instance" {
  name            = "write-replica-instance" # Write replicas has special naming
  settings {
    disk_size_gb   = 100
    disk_type      = "pd-ssd"
  }
}
```
In the code above, please ensure to replace "your-gcp-project-id", "your-gcp-region", and other placeholder values with the actual values relevant to your project. Adjust the backup, network, and IP configuration if necessary.

