Notes:
1. The S3 bucket is configured to host static content and lambda functions for image uploads.
2. AWS API Gateway is set up to receive image uploads via POST requests and serve random cat images via GET requests.
3. CloudFront distribution is used to serve images through API Gateway domain name matching. 

To handle image uploads through your AWS API Gateway, your AWS Lambda function needs permissions from API Gateway to invoke, enhancing your infrastructure to ensure seamless operation in the hosting solution.

This setup assumes that AWS API Gateway has access permissions and AWS Lambda function provides the integration with S3, similar to the configurations for uploads demonstrated earlier in the code. Additionally, CloudFront distribution settings augment the setup to ensure images are served securely.

