  value = google_cloud_sql_instance.mysql_instance.name
}
```

This configuration creates a VPC with two subnetworks, one public for general use and another with restricted access for database use. Additionally, it provisions a MySQL database instance and configures its networking to ensure access only through specific security groups by leveraging Google's Cloud SQL Instance and Networking configuration resources. Note that you might need to adjust the CIDR blocks and other specific settings according to your actual requirements and Google Cloud policies.

